ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# PORT=3001

# AnkiConnect (Anki must be open with AnkiConnect add-on installed)
# ANKI_URL=http://localhost:8765
# ANKI_COMPANION_DECK=Companion       ← deck for new cards created by the companion
# ANKI_COMPANION_MODEL=Companion      ← note type for new cards (auto-created on first use)
#
# Audio: new Companion cards use Anki's built-in {{tts}} in the card template,
# which reads the Sentence field using your system's Japanese TTS voices (no extra software needed).
# When updating existing cards (Kaishi etc.), the old sentence audio is cleared and the same
# {{tts}} tag is appended to that note type's back template on the first update.
#
# To use premium macOS voices instead of the default system voice, set ANKI_TTS_VOICES to a
# comma-separated list of voice IDs. Check available voices in System Settings → Accessibility →
# Spoken Content → System Voice → Manage Voices. Voice IDs use the Apple_ prefix.
# ANKI_TTS_VOICES=Apple_Kyoko_(Enhanced),Apple_Otoya_(Enhanced)
# (run `say -v '?' | grep ja_JP` to list installed voices; Anki ID = Apple_ + name with spaces→underscores)
#
# Existing card templates with bare {{tts ja_JP:...}} tags are automatically upgraded to include
# the voices list the next time you send a sentence to that note type.
